-- Hong Kong shares end flat, Kunlun jumps 
-- By Grace Li
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 04:12AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 17 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's benchmark index ended flat on Thursday, dampened by a weak Macau gaming sector and a retreat by Internet giant Tencent.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended a tick lower at 23,520.87 points, after three days of gains. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong was down 0.1 percent. The biggest drag, Tencent <0700.HK>, ended a three-day rally with a drop of 0.6 percent.  Shares of Macau casino Sands China <1928.HK> fell 1.2 percent after the company reported weaker-than-expected earnings. [ID:nH9N0PD015] Sector rival Galaxy Entertainment Group <0027.HK> also lost 1.2 percent.